[FIXME Confirm][From ML]If your screensaver (mind you, NOT other opengl stuff) 
is running yucky and you use a 3dfx card, try editing the .xscreensaver 
file in your home directory. there's a little stanza that looks like this:
<example>
nice:           10
memoryLimit:    0M
fade:           True
</example>
by default, xscreensaver wrote this file with a memoryLimit of 50M!!!
